# set kya hota hai?# set ek aisa data structure hai jo unique elements ko store karta hai. Isme duplicate values nahi hoti hain. Set unordered hota hai, iska matlab hai ki isme elements kisi specific order mein nahi hote hain. Set ko curly braces {} ke andar likha jata hai, aur elements comma se separated hote hain. Set mein hum kisi bhi type ke data ko store kar sakte hain, jaise ki integers, strings, ya phir tuples. Set mein hum elements ko add, remove, aur check kar sakte hain. Set ke kuch common operations hain: union, intersection, difference, aur symmetric difference. Set ka use tab hota hai jab hume unique elements ko store karna hota hai, ya phir jab hume set operations perform karne hote hain. Set ka use data analysis, machine learning, aur programming mein hota hai.